(7, 31, 27, 'How to learn English to be internationally employable', NULL, 'Hi, my goal would be learning English (this question I am writing with the help of a friend) to a level that I would be employable in international environment.', '<p>I am a SW developer and want to get employed in international firm. I suspect there I would need to be able to handle read / written English to understand well the specifications and team online collaborative tools as Slack or Trello, and spoken English to be able to handle international conference call without a translating help.<br></p>', '<p>I am Indian native, and in English I can handle reading technical / coding articles, but I am worse in written English (my grammar is rather imperfect and my written English, without a friend''s help, probably does not sound really English). I cannot read English books much - both the vocabulary and more complicated phrases are making that difficult for me to really comprehend and enjoy the reading. In spoken English, I again can comprehend a technical talk when it is slow and clearly spoken; much worse is my understanding of a general spoken English (eg, movies without subtitles are difficult for me). My spoken English is clumsy, basis and I suspect it sounds more Indian than English in terms of accent.<br></p>', '<p>I would be the most interest in an online way how to improve my English; I am having in mind a budget of tens up to hundred(s) of USD, depending on the quality of the learning resource. I would need to see an improvement in, say, 4-6 months - to be able to apply for an international job with a good chances.<br></p>', '<p>Online / over the web would be best; I do not know however whether it would allow also for spoken English practices?<br></p>', 'Y', 'N', 'U', 55, 'A', '2017-08-24 20:27:10', '2018-03-18 20:54:51'),
(8, 30, 21, 'Self-presentation courses - when becoming a freelancer', NULL, 'Hi All, my question is following: I have worked as a typist / typesetter in a text editing and printing company. Now I want to go independent and start, perhaps initially, as a freelancer in the field, and later on maybe establish my own small company. I know I need to learn accounting etc and a basis law, but most of all I feel I need to get the skill (or confidence?) how to present myself or my work. Any recommendation how to learn it?', '<p>To confidently present myself (as a professional in my field) and my work when meeting prospective clients and applying for jobs and projects in my field.<br></p>', 'I know how to prepare visually good presentations in powerpoint and similar tools. I can normally speak well to unknown people - but, when speaking to business prospects when I need to "pitch" myself and getting or not getting the job from them is at stake, I am less confident, and this "game" is having certain specific rules, compared to an informal talk.<br>', '<p>I am having on mind a budget of a couple of USD 100s. But, maybe, good learning could also be out there for free - I just do not know.<br></p>', '<p>I am not against an online way of learning. I however feel, that this "self-presentation" learning will entail to practicing, which may not be that easy to do online and better might be in person/<br></p>', 'Y', 'N', 'U', 135, 'A', '2017-08-31 12:58:19', '2018-04-25 19:06:52'),
(9, 28, 27, 'Learning Data Science', NULL, 'Hi all, I am having decent Python and PHP coding skills, and want to become a Data Scientist. What learning path should I take?', 'To be proficient at the classical data science algorithms and models (eg, decision trees, clustering, various regressions and classification models etc). AT the beginning, I probably do not aspire to be too good in deep learning, which I read about is an advanced topic - so I want to start from where the need is.<br>', 'I know well how to code in PHP and Python. I am coding web applications in PHP. In Python, I am writing scripts automating repetitive tasks, thus know all of Python variably types, classes / methods / etc, list comprehensions and so on. I know NumPy to an extent.<br>', '<p>Budget depends on the choices. If there is a good online course, then I think of spending USD 100s. If in-person bootcamp, then I would think of a couple of USD 1000s. My other constraint is time: ideally, I want to study along my existing daily job. However, I could perhaps spare some 2-3 months for full time study too, but not more.<br></p>', '<p>I learned my coding from the online tutorials mostly, but Data Science seems to be more involved and I am afraid of ending us as "useless amateur" if go solely online. Thus online interactive course would be a minimum I think, but the more in=person training to really learn, the better.<br></p>', 'Y', 'N', 'U', 63, 'A', '2017-09-08 19:11:33', '2018-04-29 07:55:17'),
(10, 31, 34, 'How to learn Spanish well?', NULL, 'Would you recommend me a learning path, and an institution, to learn the Spanish language from scratch?', '<p>First, to grasp the Spanish on a conversational level. Second, to be able to read books in Spanish. Third, to understand TV and movies in Spanish. In this order.<br></p>', 'I just understand a few words, otherwise I speak English as foreign language decently well. My native is Czech.', '<p>I would be happy to spend a budget of app USD 1-3 th. on it, depending on the intensity. I probably can spare 1 hour per day, and some 2 hours at selected days.<br></p>', '<p>Well, one on one or a small class would be great; I however can think of a combination of offline learning of the grammar and vocabulary, and face to face for corrections and conversation.<br></p>', 'Y', 'N', 'U', 114, 'A', '2017-09-10 20:40:18', '2018-04-21 10:37:06');
