(12, 10, 40, '<p>I think (and, it is unfortunately not my first-hand experience) that great way to learn Spanish (or any foreign language, if it comes to it) is, if you can afford it time-wise, to spend a good time - I mean at least between 3-6 months - in country where the language is spoken. Going to Spain would, of course, be great, but recall Spanish is spoken across Latin America and I heard really exciting stories about learning Spanish in, eg, the Ecuadorean city Cuenca, which sits in the middle of Andes, is very affordable money-wise (esp for people from Europe or North America), hosts a number of universities offering Spanish language courses (see eg here&nbsp;<a href="https://studyabroad.unm.edu/student-programs/university-cuenca-spanish-foreigners-program-intensive-language-program">University of Cuence Spanish programme</a> ) and, of course, offers the Spanish-spoken everyday life experience. The dream of mine as a Spanish learner! Anyone out there who could describe such experience first-hand?<br></p>', '<p>I have not been through the above, unfortunately. My - erratic, just basic - spoken Spanish has been acquired mostly during a number of trips to and throughout Spain.<br></p>', '<p>To be seen yet!<br></p>', NULL, 'A', '110.227.73.213', '2017-10-07 21:02:46', '2018-02-05 11:11:02'),
(13, 9, 34, '<p>AAA<br></p>', '<p>BBB<br></p>', '<p>CCC<br></p>', NULL, 'I', '46.135.79.231', '2017-10-22 12:01:36', '2017-10-22 12:01:36'),
(14, 10, 27, '<p>Hi, I am not any expert on how to learn Spanish myself, but I heard that really good path for Spanish is to enroll to courses offered by <a href="http://www.cervantes.es/default.htm">Instituto Cervantes.</a></p><p>This is non-profit organisation active, I guess, in many countries across the world and (similarly to, eg, the German Goethe Institute) is dedicated to providing an access to Spanish cultural heritage, language, etc. I think they are having many in-person courses both for beginners and advanced students, conversation lessons etc.<br><br></p>', '<p>I myself have been through, years ago, a book-based self-learning course (I have no modern online course experience unfortunately - would want to try one once). It took me a bit forward in terms of learning vocabulary and understanding a bit the written Spanish, but did not help in speaking or comprehending the spoken Spanish.<br></p>', '<p>The self-taught book-based approach, as I wrote above, helped me to understand a bit written Spanish, but did not help much with spoken Spanish.<br></p><p><br></p><p></p>', NULL, 'A', '47.15.9.41', '2017-10-29 19:12:54', '2018-02-05 10:47:47'),
(15, 9, 34, '<p>I tinkered a bit with MOOCs, but then decided to go to a bootcamp for learning Data Science (my background was math, but not much coding). There are a number of in the US and a few in Europe, depending from where you are - my ultimate choice, after a bit of research, was DSR - Data Science Retreat in Berlin, Germany - <a href="https://www.datascienceretreat.com/">https://www.datascienceretreat.com/</a>. It may or may not fit your budget - it took EUR 10k in my time; also, it takes 3 months full time on the spot, and there is no escape from it if you want it really intensive.<br></p>', '<p>Overall, very good. I was initially weaker in (Python) coding than the most of others (9 participants in my class), so was a bit lost in Docker / Linux / Spark etc issues, but after a while I found the ground and then the learning was a pleasure. Very practical, hands on, lecturers being solely professional data scientists from Berlin businesses. No academical theory, all to the practical point. Most of the curriculum was "classical" DS, although there also was a section on Deep Learning (image processing / conv nets).<br></p>', '<p>In 3 months I managed to be decently skilled in Data Science. Nowadays I am working in the DS field in business, and being confident in the classical DS in Python; I am now also progressing with Deep Learning myself, through online MOOCs and self-study - which is easier with the solid grounding the classical DS.<br></p>', NULL, 'A', '90.179.53.6', '2017-11-12 11:49:12', '2018-01-28 21:39:48'),
